extends layout

block content
  style.
    .privacy-container {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 800px;
      padding: 40px 20px;
      font-family: "Lucida Grande", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #222;
    }
    .privacy-container h1 {
      font-size: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .privacy-container h2 {
      font-size: 18px;
      margin-top: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
      padding-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .privacy-container p {
      font-size: 15px;
      margin: 12px 0;
    }
    .privacy-container ol {
      padding-left: 24px;
    }
    .privacy-container ol li {
      margin: 6px 0;
    }
    .privacy-container ul {
      padding-left: 24px;
    }
    .privacy-container ul li {
      margin: 6px 0;
    }
    .privacy-container .last-updated {
      color: #666;
      font-size: 13px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .privacy-container .contact-block {
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

  .privacy-container
    h1 Fit With Friends Privacy Policy
    p.last-updated Last updated April 6, 2026

    p
      | Fit With Friends ("we", "us", or "our") respects the privacy of our users ("user" or "you"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application (the "Application"). Please read this Privacy Policy carefully.
      |
      strong IF YOU DO NOT AGREE WITH THE TERMS OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY, PLEASE DO NOT ACCESS THE APPLICATION.

    p We reserve the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy at any time and for any reason. We will alert you about any changes by updating the "Last updated" date of this Privacy Policy. You are encouraged to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed of updates. Your continued use of the Application after any changes to this Privacy Policy constitutes your acceptance of those changes.

    h2 Collection of Your Information

    p We collect the following information when you use the Application:

    p
      strong Account Information
    p When you sign in using Apple Sign-In, we receive and store a unique identifier associated with your Apple account. We do not receive or store your email address. During account creation, we collect your first and last name (as provided by Apple Sign-In) which are used as your display name and are visible to other users in your competitions. You can update your name within the Application at any time.

    p
      strong Health and Fitness Data
    p With your permission, the Application reads the following data from Apple HealthKit:
    ul
      li
        strong Activity summaries:
        |  daily active calories burned, exercise minutes, and stand hours, along with your corresponding daily goals for each metric
      li
        strong Workouts:
        |  workout type, duration, distance, and calories burned for individual workout sessions
      li
        strong Additional metrics:
        |  step count, walking/running distance, and flights climbed
    p This data is uploaded to our servers so it can be compared against other users in your competitions. The Application observes changes to your HealthKit data in the background so it can sync updated activity automatically. We do not write any data to HealthKit.

    p
      strong Push Notification Tokens
    p If you opt in to push notifications, we store a device token provided by Apple Push Notification service (APNs) along with an app installation identifier so that we can send you notifications related to your competitions.

    p
      strong Subscription Information
    p If you subscribe to Fit With Friends Pro, we validate your subscription status through Apple's App Store. We store whether your account has an active Pro subscription, along with a transaction identifier and subscription expiration date provided by Apple. All payment processing is handled entirely by Apple — we do not collect or store any payment information such as credit card numbers or billing addresses.

    p
      strong Technical Data
    p We collect your device's timezone setting (e.g., "America/New_York") for competition scheduling purposes, and your app version to check for required updates. We do not collect device model, operating system version, or other device identifiers.

    h2 Information We Do NOT Collect

    p To be clear about the scope of our data collection, the Application does not:

    ul
      li Collect your location or geo-location data
      li Access your contacts, photos, camera, or microphone
      li Use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs
      li Collect device information such as device model, operating system version, or phone number
      li Send you marketing emails or newsletters
      li Sell or share your data with third parties for advertising or marketing purposes

    h2 Use of Your Information

    p We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

    ol
      li To create and manage your account
      li To display your activity data within competitions you have joined, so you and other competition members can compare fitness progress
      li To send you push notifications related to your competitions (if you have opted in)
      li To validate and manage your Pro subscription status
      li To operate and maintain the Application

    h2 Disclosure of Your Information

    p Your information may be shared in the following limited circumstances:

    p
      strong Other Users in Your Competitions
    p Your display name and fitness data (activity summaries, workout data, and related metrics) are visible to other members of competitions you have joined. Public competitions are visible to all users of the Application.

    p
      strong Service Providers
    p We use the following services to operate the Application:
    ul
      li
        strong Apple Sign-In
        |  — for account authentication
      li
        strong Apple Push Notification service (APNs)
        |  — for delivering push notifications
      li
        strong Apple App Store
        |  — for processing subscriptions and validating receipts
      li
        strong Microsoft Azure
        |  — for hosting our servers and database

    p
      strong By Law or to Protect Rights
    p We may disclose your information if required by law or if we believe disclosure is necessary to comply with a legal obligation, protect our rights, or ensure the safety of our users.

    p
      strong Sale or Bankruptcy
    p If we reorganize or sell all or a portion of our assets, undergo a merger, or are acquired by another entity, we may transfer your information to the successor entity. If we go out of business or enter bankruptcy, your information would be an asset transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur and that the transferee may decline to honor commitments we made in this Privacy Policy.

    h2 Security of Your Information

    p We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your personal information. Authentication tokens are stored securely on your device using the iOS Keychain. However, no method of data transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security of your information.

    h2 Policy for Children

    p We do not knowingly solicit information from or market to children under the age of 13. If you become aware of any data we have collected from children under age 13, please contact us using the contact information provided below.

    h2 Your Choices

    p You have the following options regarding your information:

    ul
      li
        strong HealthKit Access:
        |  You can revoke the Application's access to your HealthKit data at any time through your device's Settings > Health > Data Access.
      li
        strong Push Notifications:
        |  You can disable push notifications at any time through your device's Settings.
      li
        strong Display Name:
        |  You can update your display name within the Application.
      li
        strong Account Deletion:
        |  You may request deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us at the email address below. Upon request, we will delete your account and personal information from our active databases.

    h2 California Privacy Rights

    p California Civil Code Section 1798.83 permits our users who are California residents to request and obtain from us, once a year and free of charge, information about categories of personal information (if any) we disclosed to third parties for direct marketing purposes. We do not disclose personal information to third parties for direct marketing purposes.

    p If you are under 18 years of age, reside in California, and have a registered account with the Application, you have the right to request removal of unwanted data that you publicly post on the Application. To request removal of such data, please contact us using the contact information provided below.

    h2 Contact Us

    p If you have questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

    .contact-block
      p Fit With Friends
      p
        a(href='mailto:fitwithfriendsapp@gmail.com') fitwithfriendsapp@gmail.com
